				\begin{document}$$\Delta \varvec{r}^{*}$$\end{document}. Based on the work of Waldspurger et al.57, we approximate this phase retrieval problem by transforming it into a convex semidefinite program (SDP)58 called PhaseCut57, which is similar to the well-known MaxCut59 problem. This allows us to apply recent results for MaxCut to PhaseCut and to develop a greedy algorithm based on techniques like the Burer–Monteiro method60,61 and block-coordinate minimisation (BCM)62. As a result, our proposed algorithm provides both high convergence rate and low execution time, solving PhaseCut in up to \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
